{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "15", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "38", "S": "07"}}, "news": [{"title": "Lucknow: LDA to draft GIS-based master plan 2051 for six districts included in state capital region", "para": "Lucknow Development Authority is preparing a GIS-based Master Plan-2051 for the Uttar Pradesh State Capital Region. This digital plan will integrate land use and development projects across six districts on one platform. The regional master plan will define land use, settlement patterns, and transport networks for planned growth. It proposes new highways, rail links, and mass transit systems for coordinated development.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/lda-to-create-gis-based-master-plan-2051-for-uttar-pradesh-state-capital-region/132405886?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-625831/132405886.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Gurugram: A decade after moving in, 206 Unitech Fresco families get OCs for their flats", "para": "Unitech Fresco residents in Gurgaon finally received occupation certificates for their homes.  This long-awaited approval brings legal certainty to 206 families living in four towers.  The certificates were issued by the town and country planning department after extensive verification processes.  Residents expressed immense relief after years of facing complications with property registrations and loans.  This development marks the resolution of a significant pending issue for the society.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/206-families-in-unitech-fresco-finally-receive-occupation-certificates-after-a-decade-long-wait/132405597?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1304966/132405597.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Sebi exempts Mehta Family Trust from Saurashtra Cement open offer", "para": "Sebi exempted Mehta Family Trust from an open offer for Saurashtra Cement shares.  This exemption allows internal family reorganisation and succession planning.  Jay Mahendra Mehta and Juhi Chawla Mehta are trustees of the family trust.  The transaction involves indirect acquisition of shares and voting rights.  This exemption is valid for one year from the order date.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/sebi-grants-exemption-to-mehta-family-trust-for-saurashtra-cement-acquisition/132405297?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-500749/132405297.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}]}